The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Tuesday, September 24, 2002 				 Streak hurt in road accident
				 	 STREAK: Parting blow																								Colombo: Zimbabwe captain Heath Streak was taken to hospital with a shoulder injury suffered in a road accident on Monday, a team official said.																								He seems to have dislocated or stretched his shoulder and collar bone, but it is not a major injury, the teams liaison officer said.																								The fast bowler was travelling in a three-wheeler taxi in Colombo when the vehicle overturned trying to avoid a car, he said. 																								Streak, whose team has been eliminated from the Champions Trophy, will spend the night in hospital.																								Zimbabwe were with India and England in pool 2 and lost both matches. (REUTERS)
